\title{Own Goal}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{Save session goals to org files in the goals-*.org format. Auto-increments rank, classifies theme, writes org entry with properties and task checklist.}

\subtree{
\title{Own Goal}
\p{Save the current session's goal to the goals org file at \code{\startverb/Users/alice/v/goals-119.org\stopverb}. Each entry gets an auto-incremented rank, a theme classification, TODO state, and a task checklist.}

\subtree{
\title{Usage}
\p{When the user says \code{\startverb/own-goal\stopverb} or asks to "save own goal", do this:}

\ol{
\li{Run \code{\startverbscripts/next-rank.sh\stopverb} to get the next rank number}
\li{Ask the user for a one-line goal summary (or infer from session context)}
\li{Classify into a theme from the table below}
\li{Choose a TODO state: \code{\startverbSTARTED\stopverb}, \code{\startverbIN_PROGRESS\stopverb}, \code{\startverbSUBSTANTIAL\stopverb}, \code{\startverbABANDONED\stopverb}, or \code{\startverbCOMPLETED\stopverb}}
\li{Append the org entry to \code{\startverb/Users/alice/v/goals-119.org\stopverb} before the \code{\startverb* Cross-References\stopverb} section}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Theme Classification}
